stylometry:
You use sensitivity analysis to find out how changing a certain input will effect your desired result. If one variable changes, others will adjust accordingly. You can use it to see what areas you should focus on. It shows the sensibility of a problem and how vulnerable and easy it is subject to change.

You would run solver table at the end of your analysis to find the optimal solution to whatever it is that you are trying to figure out and calculate. You need to enter in your target cell, changing cells, and constraints, and then excel will run through the multiple feasible solutions, and deliver the "best value" or optimal result.
